            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>
                    Sacred to the Shades of the Underworld. To Gaius Pomponius Vitalis, son of Gaius, flamen of the divine Vespasian, aedile of Terventum [and]
                    to Gaius Pomponius Marcellinus, son of Gaius, public equestrian, patron of the municipium of Terventum, aedile.
                    Gaius Pomponius Vitalis, son of Gaius, curator of the Via Traiana Pataesina, patron of the municipium and administrator of all honours
                    in the municipium of Terventum, flamen of the divine Trajan, judge of the 400 at Rome, of the five decuriae,
                    most unhappy father built (this).
                </p>
